<p>devil and fasted 40 days etc There is a monastery on top and another built into the precipitous side of the hill. Probably the scene which inspired the opening chapters in Scotts "Ivanhoe". The morning after our arrival we moved out to carry rations to the Divisions &amp; trekked right across the Valley crossing by a pontoon bridge over the Jordan, which is in flood just now &amp; even so not more than 50 yards across</p>
